# open-slide

The deck workspace lives in `my-deck/`. `cd my-deck` before running npm scripts; paths like `slides/` and `node_modules/.open-slide/current.json` are relative to `my-deck/`.

Author slides as React components under `my-deck/slides/<id>/index.tsx`. Read `AGENTS.md` for hard rules and which `.cursor/skills/` workflow to use.

- New deck → `create-slide` skill
- Inspector `@slide-comment` markers → `apply-comments` skill
- New theme → `create-theme` skill
- "This page" / "this element" without a name → `current-slide` skill (read `node_modules/.open-slide/current.json`)
- Any slide code edit → read `slide-authoring` **and** `pptx-design` first (every page must stay PPTX/Google Slides–editable; do not wait for an export request)
- Spin up / start servers → both **5173** (published core) and **5174** (local editable PPTX); see `spin-up-dev-servers` rule

Do not modify `package.json`, `open-slide.config.ts`, or slides you were not asked to touch. No new dependencies.
